  "mixStrategy": "This arrangement is a gentle Classical relaxation piece in G major, designed so each track occupies a distinct frequency band for a warm, spacious sound. BASS (Cello, 20-300Hz, MIDI 36-55): Provides the harmonic foundation with sustained roots and occasional 5ths, anchoring every chord change. Plays long legato notes in the C2-C4 range. CHORDS (String Ensemble, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Fills the harmonic body with close-voiced triads and 7ths, sustaining smooth pads that shift with proper voice leading\u2014common tones are held across chord changes. MELODY (Acoustic Piano, 1-8kHz, MIDI 60-79): The lead voice, playing a lyrical singable theme with antecedent-consequent phrasing. Chord tones land on strong beats, with stepwise passing tones on weak beats. TEXTURE (Flute, 3kHz+, MIDI 72-88): A sparse, ornamental counter-melody that floats above everything, adding shimmer and air with gentle phrases that breathe between the melody's statements. ENERGY ARC: Segments (~7.5s each): 0.3\u21920.5\u21920.6\u21920.7\u21920.6\u21920.4. The piece begins softly with sparse notes and low velocities, gradually builds to a gentle climax around 22-30s, then gracefully recedes. All tracks follow the same chord progression: I(G)\u2192IV(C)\u2192V(D)\u2192I(G) for the first half, then I(G)\u2192vi(Em)\u2192IV(C)\u2192V(D) for the second half. Bass always plays chord roots. Chord changes happen simultaneously across all tracks. Rhythmic interlock: bass sustains under chords, melody floats above with longer phrases, texture adds gentle filigree in the gaps.",
